						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">qbradq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You can set up a breakpoint for the PPU control registers in Nintendulator to see when it disables the rendering. Nintendulator has this nice PPU scanline and pixel counter when single-stepping.</div>
<br />Good idea!
<br />
<br />If I'm reading this correctly:
<br />
<br />SLNum: 209
<br />CPU Ticks: ranges from 306-317 / 102-105
<br />
<br />So scanline 209, but I dunno what pixel that translates to. It's outside of the 64-255 range though.
<br />
<br />(The breakpoint I set was on $E2BF, and I used fceux to find that address by looking for writes to $2001)</div>

